1️) Add remote origin 
git remote add origin https://github.com/nazmul-islam-abir/sel-group-project.git

Verify:
git remote -v

You should see:
origin  https://github.com/nazmul-islam-abir/sel-group-project.git (fetch)
origin  https://github.com/nazmul-islam-abir/sel-group-project.git (push)


2️) Switch to your local branch Abir/Alavy/Minhaj/Junayed(Pick Your Name Only)
Check branch:
git branch

git checkout -b Abir/Alavy/Minhaj/Junayed


3️) Pull remote branch to sync
git pull origin Abir/Alavy/Minhaj/Junayed --rebase



4️) Add & commit any new files
git add .
git commit -m "Added files to Abir/Alavy/Minhaj/Junayed branch"


5️) Push your branch to GitHub
git push -u origin Abir/Alavy/Minhaj/Junayed

✅ Done! Now your local Abir branch is synced with remote and all files are pushed.

Optional: Future pushes
From now on, you can just run:
git push

No need to specify origin or branch again.

